This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification using Convolutional Neural Networks. It also involves deep learning architectures, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The methodology proposed in the paper involves reducing the computation and memory requirements of CNN models, which makes it relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves testing the methodology on a dataset, which makes it relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
